<subSubSection id="C31F78D00C1C8D68FF5FFCEEFD6869F4" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBA2B5B0C1C8D68FF5FFCEEFD6869F4" blockId="8.[151,1437,823,1749]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FF5FFCEEFE996E78" bold="true" box="[151,273,823,848]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Average forewing length: males 
<quantity id="4CFD86BE0C1C8D68FD5BFCE1FC866E67" box="[659,782,824,848]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="13.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="12.0">12–14 mm</quantity>
(n = 6), females 
<quantity id="4CFD86BE0C1C8D68FC13FCEEFB096E67" box="[987,1153,823,848]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.385" metricValueMax="1.45" metricValueMin="1.3199999999999998" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="13.85" valueMax="14.5" valueMin="13.2">13.2–14.5 mm</quantity>
(n = 3). This taxon was originally described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FD94FC85FD436E5C" box="[604,715,860,884]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Audre" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FD94FC85FD436E5C" box="[604,715,860,884]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its similarities and allopatric distribution (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9456AA0C1C8D68FAC1FC85FEAF6EB0" author="Callaghan" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" refString="Callaghan, C. J. &amp; Soares, A. (2001) A review of the Cinericiiformes section of the genus Audre Hemming and the description of a new subspecies (Riodinidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 18 (3), 755 - 763. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0101 - 81752001000300012" type="journal article" year="2001">Callaghan &amp; Soares 2001</bibRefCitation>
). However, more detailed evaluation of its morphology combined with the differences in the 
<collectionCode id="ED14B39E0C1C8D68FAA8FC59FA156EB0" box="[1376,1437,896,920]" country="Australia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" name="Department of Natural Resources, Environment, The Arts and Sport" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">DNA</collectionCode>
barcode (3.91%, 
<tableCitation id="C6871EE00C1C8D68FE90FC7DFE256E94" box="[344,429,932,957]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,239,691,714]" captionText="TABLE 2. Comparison of inter- and intraspecific divergences (%) for the DNA “ barcodes ” of Sertania gen. nov. species (number of individuals in parentheses). Values of divergence above 2 percent are in bold; (--) does not apply." pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Table 2</tableCitation>
) indicate that the differences are more profound and that 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FBF5FC7DFB366E94" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[1085,1214,932,956]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FBF5FC7DFB366E94" box="[1085,1214,932,956]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be raised to species status. The FW shape of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FDCEFC11FD596EC8" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[518,721,968,992]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FDCEFC11FD596EC8" box="[518,721,968,992]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Sertania jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2424A320C1C8D68FD1FFC1EFC426EC8" box="[727,970,967,992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FD1FFC1EFC426EC8" bold="true" box="[727,970,967,992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">comb. nov., stat nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FB97FC11FA9C6EC8" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1119,1300,968,992]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FB97FC11FA9C6EC8" box="[1119,1300,968,992]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Sertania guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2424A320C1C8D68FAD3FC1EFA146EC8" box="[1307,1436,967,992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FAD3FC1EFA146EC8" bold="true" box="[1307,1436,967,992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">comb. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in being relatively longer with a more pointed apex and the margin of both wing surfaces black instead of red; the male ventral HW post-medial area is nearly white in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FCCAFBC9FC0D6900" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[770,901,1040,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FCCAFBC9FC0D6900" box="[770,901,1040,1064]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and dark brown in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FBA5FBC9FB536900" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1133,1243,1040,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FBA5FBC9FB536900" box="[1133,1243,1040,1064]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The frons of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FA4FFBC9FF736964" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FA4FFBC9FF736964" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is dark brown with a small white spot in the middle; that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FC09FBEDFBA76964" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[961,1071,1076,1100]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FC09FBEDFBA76964" box="[961,1071,1076,1100]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is white with two parallel light brown vertical lines. In the male genitalia, valvae are slightly longer with tips turned up in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FB71FB81FAAE6958" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1209,1318,1112,1136]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FB71FB81FAAE6958" box="[1209,1318,1112,1136]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="133E37DE0C1C8D68FAF1FB8EFA076958" box="[1337,1423,1111,1136]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[171,1428,481,1280]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1428,481,1280]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 26. Male genitalia of Sertania gen. nov. species. 19 – 22, Sertania guttata comb. nov. from Punta de los Llanos, La Rioja, Argentina (ZUEC), lateral view (19), tegumen and uncus in dorsal view (20), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (21), valvae in lateral view (22). 23 – 24, Sertania jaibensis comb. nov., stat. nov. paratype from Diamantina, Minas Gerais, Brazil (DZUP), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (23), valvae in lateral view (24). 25 – 26, Sertania lambedor comb. nov., stat. nov. from Ibimirim, Pernambuco, Brazil (ZUEC), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (25), valvae in lateral view (26). Scale bars = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892883/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
), while they are shorter and truncated with straight tips in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FCC7FBA5FC0769BC" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[783,911,1148,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FCC7FBA5FC0769BC" box="[783,911,1148,1172]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="133E37DE0C1C8D68FC56FBA5FC7A69BC" box="[926,1010,1148,1173]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1302,1324]" captionTargetBox="[171,1428,481,1280]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1428,481,1280]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 26. Male genitalia of Sertania gen. nov. species. 19 – 22, Sertania guttata comb. nov. from Punta de los Llanos, La Rioja, Argentina (ZUEC), lateral view (19), tegumen and uncus in dorsal view (20), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (21), valvae in lateral view (22). 23 – 24, Sertania jaibensis comb. nov., stat. nov. paratype from Diamantina, Minas Gerais, Brazil (DZUP), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (23), valvae in lateral view (24). 25 – 26, Sertania lambedor comb. nov., stat. nov. from Ibimirim, Pernambuco, Brazil (ZUEC), tegumen and uncus in lateral view (25), valvae in lateral view (26). Scale bars = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892883/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
); the pedicel is straight and pointed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FF5FFB79FE8A6990" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[151,258,1184,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FF5FFB79FE8A6990" box="[151,258,1184,1208]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and more curved and separated in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FD58FB79FC986990" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[656,784,1184,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FD58FB79FC986990" box="[656,784,1184,1208]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the female genitalia, the ostium bursae is broader in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FA4FFB79FF6E69F4" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FA4FFB79FF6E69F4" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and more constricted caudad in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FD91FB1DFD5169F4" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[601,729,1220,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FD91FB1DFD5169F4" box="[601,729,1220,1244]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31F78D00C1C8D68FF0FFB3EFB9F6B6D" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BBA2B5B0C1C8D68FF0FFB3EFB9F6B6D" blockId="8.[151,1437,823,1749]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FF0FFB3EFE7E6828" bold="true" box="[199,502,1255,1280]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Biology and distribution.</emphasis>
The habitat of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FD62FB31FCA46828" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[682,812,1256,1280]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jaibensis">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FD62FB31FCA46828" box="[682,812,1256,1280]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is transition between cerrado and caatinga vegetation. The 
<typeStatus id="54BE95F90C1C8D68FF01FAD4FF71680D" box="[201,249,1293,1317]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">type</typeStatus>
locality between Jaíba and Mocambinho (
<quantity id="4CFD86BE0C1C8D68FD19FAD5FC93680C" box="[721,795,1292,1316]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" unit="m" value="490.0">490 m</quantity>
) in the 
<collectingRegion id="49C1E5B90C1C8D68FCA7FAD5FB8C680D" box="[879,1028,1292,1317]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
state presents a closed, tall-shrubby, xerophilous vegetation termed “Carrasco” with floristic elements of caatinga (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9456AA0C1C8D68FBC1FAF6FAB96860" author="Callaghan" box="[1033,1329,1327,1352]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" refString="Callaghan, C. J. &amp; Soares, A. (2001) A review of the Cinericiiformes section of the genus Audre Hemming and the description of a new subspecies (Riodinidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 18 (3), 755 - 763. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / s 0101 - 81752001000300012" type="journal article" year="2001">Callaghan &amp; Soares 2001</bibRefCitation>
). Besides the proximity of the São 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FE7BFA8DFD7C6844" baseAuthorityName="Callaghan &amp; Soares" baseAuthorityYear="2001" box="[435,756,1364,1389]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="guttata" subSpecies="jaibensis">
Francisco River, 
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FDBBFA8DFD7C6844" box="[627,756,1364,1388]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. jaibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not inhabit gallery forests, which also form part of the habitat. The other two known localities in Diamantina and Sempre Vivas National Park consist of unique highaltitude (
<quantity id="4CFD86BE0C1C8D68FF32FA45FE13689D" box="[250,411,1436,1461]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" unit="m" value="1200.0" valueMax="1500.0" valueMin="900.0">900 to 1500m</quantity>
) rocky outcrop vegetation (
<figureCitation id="133E37DE0C1C8D68FD1CFA45FCAE689D" box="[724,806,1436,1461]" captionStart="FIGURES 34 – 37" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1200,1222]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,194,1179]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1435,193,1179]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 34 – 37. Overview of Sertania gen. nov. habitats in South American ‘ dry diagonal’. 34 – 35, Sertania guttata comb. nov., monte vegetation (34) in Anillaco, La Rioja, and Chaco serrano (35) in Capilla del Monte, Cordoba, Argentina; 36, Sertania jaibensis comb. nov., stat. nov., rocky montane fields in Sempre Vivas National Park, Buenópolis, Minas Gerais, Brazil; 37, Sertania lambedor comb. nov., stat. nov., arboreal caatinga in Custódia, Pernambuco, Brazil. Photos (36) by CA Iserhard and (37) by DHA Melo." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892889/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
) locally known as “campos rupestres” typical of higher parts of the “Serra do Espinhaço” range (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9456AA0C1C8D68FD60FA66FC2568F0" author="Alves" box="[680,941,1471,1496]" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" refString="Alves, R. J. V. &amp; Kolbek, J. (2010) Can campo rupestre vegetation be floristically delimited based on vascular plant genera? Plant Ecology, 207, 67 - 79. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 11258 - 009 - 9654 - 8" type="journal article" year="2010">Alves &amp; Kolbek 2010</bibRefCitation>
). This species is absent from the Brazilian central Plateau to the south of this locality. Butterflies fly rapidly and close to the ground at mid-day, resting with open wings on leaf dorsal surfaces, in apparent contrast to the more sedentary behavior of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0550D80C1C8D68FB4FF9D1FB7A6B08" authorityName="Freitas" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Stichel" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1159,1266,1544,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" genus="Sertania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttata">
<emphasis id="B971F7490C1C8D68FB4FF9D1FB7A6B08" box="[1159,1266,1544,1568]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">S. guttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As mentioned above, the species is known from only three localities in northern 
<collectingRegion id="49C1E5B90C1C8D68FCB2F9F5FB9C6B6D" box="[890,1044,1580,1605]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="8" pageNumber="173">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
